[thinking] **Evaluating UintMap behavior**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how UintMap handles storing both integers and objects for the same key. If I put the object first and then the int, it seems to retain the object. When I put the int with ensureIndex set to true, it doesn’t clear the values. However, if the int is added before the object, it seems the int remains unchanged. Basically, if only an object is stored, the int defaults to 0, and if only the int is stored, the object ends up being null.
